# =====================================================================
# AlphaRavis AI Stack - Environment Configuration
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your values.
# DO NOT commit your real .env to Git.
# =====================================================================
#
# How to use this file:
#   1. Fill the MUST-HAVE section first.
#   2. Keep Docker defaults unless your ports/containers differ.
#   3. Tune optional sections only when you know what behavior you want.
#
# Section map:
#   MUST-HAVE                          -> secrets, database password, model route
#   CORE DOCKER URLS                   -> internal service URLs, usually unchanged
#   OPTIONAL REMOTE PC / SSH           -> Wake-on-LAN and SSH debugging
#   OPTIONAL MODEL / POWER MANAGEMENT  -> custom safe hooks for local hardware
#   OPTIONAL BRIDGE SETTINGS           -> LibreChat <-> LangGraph behavior
#   OPTIONAL MEMORY SETTINGS           -> compression, archives, architecture doc
#   OPTIONAL VECTOR MEMORY             -> pgvector semantic memory sidecar
#   OPTIONAL MEDIA / VISION            -> media gallery and vision embeddings
#   OPTIONAL OPENWEBUI                 -> second OpenAI-compatible frontend
#   OPTIONAL SKILL LIBRARY             -> reusable workflow skill candidates
#   OPTIONAL SEARCH                    -> Tavily / research tools
#   OPTIONAL OBSERVABILITY             -> LangSmith tracing
#   OPTIONAL LLM / CACHE / SAFETY      -> LiteLLM, Redis cache, approval gates


